      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i need to ask u something but im not sure if i sound crazy. so on my drive to work this morning, i saw the exact same gray sedan pass me three times in a row, but like... it was the same car. not just a similar car, but like the same scratches on the bumper and everything. and then the lighting on the trees just kind of flickered for a split second. i think i'm seeing things but it felt so real. does that ever happen? like are there glitches in how we see stuff?",
